MARCH 21, 1997 | Mr. Styron discussed war and racism in American literature and culture. Following his remarks, Mr. Heller and Mr. Vonnegut who are also veterans of World War II, answered questions from educators and students on their perceptions of American culture. Following their discussion, the panelists answered questions from the audience. 

